{
  "id": "019d3c7a-037f-7ba2-9c64-94c1efb09226",
  "content": "# Decision: Deep Ingest — Multi-Signal Repo Understanding (Replaces \"Codebase-to-Course\" Framing)\n\n## Context\n\nResearch (March 2026) into extracting architectural rationale from codebases found no tool combining code structure, git history, PR/issue context, and LLM synthesis. Initial framing borrowed the name \"codebase-to-course\" from an existing Claude Code skill (zarazhangrui/codebase-to-course) that generates HTML walkthroughs for humans. That name was misleading for corvia's use case.\n\n## Decisions\n\n### 1. Name: \"Deep Ingest\" (not \"codebase-to-course\")\nCorvia's feature is about corvia understanding repos for itself and the agents it serves, not generating courses for humans. \"Deep Ingest\" extends the existing `corvia workspace ingest` concept. The output is knowledge entries in the graph, not rendered content.\n\n### 2. Separate initiative, not P6\nThis is its own workstream. P6 (LLM-assisted summaries) is subsumed as Phase 1 of deep ingest. P1-P5 structural intelligence feeds into it but ships independently.\n\n### 3. Adapter-per-signal architecture\nEach knowledge signal is its own adapter. Adapters can be added, removed, or benchmarked independently.\n\n| Signal | Adapter | Status |\n|--------|---------|--------|\n| Code structure | `adapter-git` | Exists |\n| Git temporal history | `adapter-git-history` | Not started |\n| PR/issue discussion | `adapter-github` (D44) | Not started |\n| LLM synthesis | Kernel-level orchestration | Not started |\n\n### 4. Delivery by user value, not by adapter\nPhase 1 delivers user value (architectural understanding) using only existing adapter-git output. New adapters add depth in subsequent phases.\n\n### 5. Benchmark each signal independently\nMeasure per-signal contribution to synthesis quality. Deprioritize signals that don't measurably improve understanding.\n\n## Supersedes\n- Earlier \"codebase-to-course\" design entry (same session)\n- Earlier \"adapter-per-signal architecture\" decision entry (same session)\n- P6 item in Structural Intelligence roadmap (P6 is now Phase 1 of deep ingest)\n\n## Tracking\nGitHub: chunzhe10/corvia#88",
